). Gonospiculum bridge small, basal part relatively large, nearly quadrilateral and flat, apical part very short (

Figs 
16, 17

). Anterior connective lamina of gonapophysis VIII with three strong teeth in apical group and four teeth in lateral group (

Fig. 
18

). Gonocoxae VIII nearly rectangular, with hind margin concave (

Fig. 
18

).
